  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nWhen doing `forge build` on a contract repo that has some stack-too-deep scenarios, it's unclear which contracts are causing the error:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ forge build --offline\r\n[⠔] Compiling...\r\n[⠑] Compiling 38 files with 0.8.19\r\n[⠊] Solc 0.8.19 finished in 5.14s\r\nError:\r\nCompiler run failed:\r\nError: Compiler error (/solidity/libyul/backends/evm/AsmCodeGen.cpp:63):Stack too deep. Try compiling with `--via-ir` (cli) or the equivalent `viaIR: true` (standard JSON) while enabling the optimizer. Otherwise, try removing local variables. When compiling inline assembly: Variable pos is 4 slot(s) too deep inside the stack. Stack too deep. Try compiling with `--via-ir` (cli) or the equivalent `viaIR: true` (standard JSON) while enabling the optimizer. Otherwise, try removing local variables.\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if the compiler backend interface would allow surfacing this information, but would be useful if it does. Perhaps one solution is having a verbose mode for build that prints contracts it's processing as it goes.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
